how can dual diagnosis get treated i have just heard that one of my neighbors has dual diagnosis i was just wondering how this kind of illness can get treated dual diagnosis also termed co occurring disorder is characterized by a psychological illness along with a substance abuse disorder statistics show that quite a number of alcoholics and drug dependents suffer from dual diagnosis as well the two disorders must be treated simultaneously to prevent the person from relapsing there are lots of treatment centers that are now adept at handling cases like these you should probably suggest to your neighbor that he get himself checked up on by a doctor and seek treatment immediately Bipolar disorder Clinical depression Post-traumatic stress disorder Dissociative identity disorder Drug abuse Alcoholism Mental illness Anorexia nervosa Schizophrenia Involuntary commitment Hypoglycemia Multiple sclerosis Psychiatry Addiction Chronic fatigue syndrome Gender identity disorder Anxiety Drug addiction Traumatic brain injury Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Obsessive-compulsive disorder Antidepressant Stomach cancer Substance abuse Cancer Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders Adult attention-deficit disorder Pneumonia Epilepsy Stroke Homeopathy Allergy Parkinson's disease Panic attack Anti-psychiatry Controlled Substances Act Prostate cancer Asthma Urinary incontinence Folic acid Coeliac disease Lupus erythematosus Sleep apnea Doxepin Diazepam Gout Migraine Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Bupropion Hypertension Ulcerative colitis Rape Mental Health Act 1983 Charles Darwin's illness Narcolepsy Malaria National Institutes of Health Common cold Transsexuality Alternative medicine Antisocial personality disorder Chemical imbalance theory Cephalic disorder Borderline personality disorder Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Tuberculosis Electroconvulsive therapy HIV test Trimipramine Methylphenidate Autism Osteoarthritis Munchausen syndrome Alcoholics Anonymous Psychotherapy Ost